    "body": "> The issue is: in TxPool, the value of `-pricelimit` is stored in the field `gasPrice`. We apply this check when validating incoming transactions:\r\n> \r\n> https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/03bc8b7858e0b019132de5fd5df6e8ec414d1dfd/core/tx_pool.go#L624-L627\r\n> \r\n> However, we apply a different check when selecting transactions for mining:\r\n> \r\n> https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/03bc8b7858e0b019132de5fd5df6e8ec414d1dfd/core/tx_pool.go#L547-L549\r\n> \r\n> I think this issue could be resolved by making the check in `validateTx` also use the `EffectiveGasTipIntCmp` method.\r\n\r\n`pool.gasPrice` is config by `pricelimit`. \r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/cc87cbd70af18241f79908eec10bb3c51a9fbda4/core/tx_pool.go#L300\r\n\r\n`baseFee` will always changed by tx pool . so if you do that, users will not able to send tx below baseFee rather than `pricelimit`. highly recommended revert this pr  #23855.\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/cc87cbd70af18241f79908eec10bb3c51a9fbda4/core/tx_list.go#L424",
